Laying there, in the white tiger form, at the large feet of the Decepticon 
statues. She had been laying there for sometime, completely oblivious to 
time. 

She could feel all the things organics felt. Which is no welcome to her. As a 
Decepticon in years past, she despised humans, only going near a couple due 
to they were useful to Megatron & the Decepticon cause. But now... she was 
organic. A disgusting organic! Well.. partly organic. 

She sighed as she stood up. A sort of.. hunger in her urged her to move & 
search for something. It took her a moment to understand what it was. She 
needed fuel. Energon. Ummm... if she could STILL have energon & if energon 
was still available. 

She glanced about with her clear blue optics at her fallen comrades of long 
ago. Was she truely the last of the Decepticons? Why did she return? HOW did 
she return? Questions that needed to be answered... after she fould some 
energon. 

**************************

Padding along through the bowls of Cybertron, her optics kept everything in 
view. All sense were acute, most so than when she was a Decepticon. She 
smirked, she felt more like Ravage. Now she knew how he felt. 

She heard hums or machinery every so often. The lights were dim in areas, 
while in other areas they glowed brighter, or not at all. 

She came to a Cybertronian transport system. It looked like it had not been 
used in some time, as she noticed no car & further down was heavily damaged. 

Moving along, for what seemed forever, she took in what was once her home. It 
was a mix of Organic & Cybernetic. It literially sickened her. She ached for 
the Cybertron she knew. 

Memories floded back to her, odd as it was, of when she was created. It was 
but a million years after the Revolt when the Quints had been driven from 
Cybertron. She was programmed & formatted to assist the Decepticon dignitary 
Gamma Quadraine. He was her mentor for some time, until Megatron began his 
attacks & Gamma was destroyed permenently by Autobots. Over the millions of 
years, she was in & out of battles, as the Decepticons took Cybertron, 
conquering it. She had her own missions & usually fulfilled them. 

An image then formed & was clearly stuck in her mind.. Megatron. Her leader. 
The one she swore to serve & protect. Loyal to him.. & ONLY him.  

&quot;Maxima,&quot; a muffled, deep voice stated. &quot;Maxima.&quot;

She snapped out of it, finding herself at a walkway with a huge sphere of 
light hovered in the center. Blinking, she stood there. 

&quot;Come forth, Maxima,&quot;

She looked oddly at the ball of light. &quot;Who are you?&quot; 

A scratchy voice slowly escaped the light, &quot;Before Cybertron was, I was.&quot; 

Her optics grew, she knew it, having visited the place a couple times. But it 
had changed now. &quot;Vector Sigma,&quot; 

Then the voice changed again, to a raspy old voice, &quot;Aye.&quot;

She growled in a little annoyance. &quot;What do you want, old fool,&quot; Maxima 
glared at the light. 

&quot;To help you,&quot; the raspy old voice returned. 

Snorting, &quot;HA! You did this to me, didn&#39;t you!? Turning me into this.. 
horrid, disgusting, aweful ORGANIC!&quot; She growled. 

&quot;It had to be done.&quot; 

&quot;NO! I want my old body back. I want to be the Decepticon I once was, Alpha 
Trion. not what YOU want me to be!&quot; 

&quot;I&#39;m sorry, but it was the only way-&quot; 

&quot;BLOODY HELL IT WAS!&quot; She growled, her feline voice booming in the open 
chamber. 

She turned around. &quot;Spare me your concern, Alpha Trion. I&#39;m a Decepticon & 
always will be .. a Decepticon. NOTHING will change that!&quot; Growling, as she 
turned her back upon the light & padded out of the chamber, away from the 
sphere of light. 

Padding through the corridors of Cybertron, she seemed to be going up towards 
the surface. &quot;I SHALL return to my old form. I shall be who I was before,&quot; 
She stated to herself. Angered with what had occured. She felt betrayed. 
Another reason she hated Autobots. They destroy everything she knew, believed 
in, even.. loved. Her comrades, her home.. everything was gone thanks to 
them!


